The paper deals with deep learning-based methods for learning functional representations of mammalian neural images, specifically in situ hybridization (ISH) images. This involves the use of deep convolutional denoising autoencoders (CDAE) for generating an invariant, compact representation of these images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also deals with classification of gene ontology categories, which involves machine learning techniques. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. 

The paper also deals with neural images, which is a topic related to neuroscience. This makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. 

Finally, the paper deals with bio-imaging analysis, which is a topic related to biology. This makes cs.BIO (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) a possible category as well.
